commit.message: LinkedIn review following changes to ToS on 03/10/2014 (effective 23/10/2014)
Changed JDM wording
Complete rewrite of all ToS services with attribute (name) order stability such that future ToS edits are easier to compare
One facebook deeplink URL fixed from http->https
Facebook deeplinks changed due to github iOS-App-a2#229 (domain now: fb.com and all URLs are https based) - also refreshed a couple of them that have since changed (e.g. apps permissions)

Added linkid to each deeplink, which will be used by app to submit piwik
stats and act as a unique identifier

Minor data fix removing source-date as it's only used in one point/service
in the whole data set

Datafix to change some service->class values from boolean to empty string
as the field is used for ratings A-D as well

Minor changes to make ToS UTF-8 compliant following from Google Doc
character punctuation "hash" in different character set

Merge branch 'mortendev' into editor

Conflicts:
	ToS/google.json
	ToS/twitter.json
G+ review - fixes #7
Facebook review - issue #2
Manual data fix to fix id of points such that they're unique

Data cleanup - loads of crappy, outdated, empty, inconsistent, incoherent
stuff
Deeplink and JDM changes

Amended all services with deeplinks section template - except for
facebook&twitter we actually have data
Fixed syntax errors caused by missing quote
Added deeplinks to the 6 services that they existed for on Alpha server

Added 4 services and amended a total of 30 services with icon information
from static content servers (URIs only)
Removed all HTML tags in content
Amended /ToS/facebook.json
First cut
